{"key":"post-11766002","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11766002</id>\n<content>Verm will increase the performance of any bulk substrate substantially.&amp;nbsp; You don't 'need' verm, nor do you 'need' gypsum, but both will pay far more in returns than their cost and extra effort.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You don't want to leach your substrate by soaking in water.&amp;nbsp; Simply hydrate to field capacity, and then load into jars or bags and drop into a pan of water that you then heat to boiling.&amp;nbsp; Stick a meat thermometer into the center of the substrate, and time one hour from the time the center reaches 140F/60C.&amp;nbsp; Try not to let the temperature exceed 160F/70C.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11770321</next>\n<prev>11765969</prev>\n<first>11764942</first>\n<last>11770392</last>\n<when>1262646614</when>\n<utime>01/05/10 01:10 AM</utime>\n</post>"}